obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2431  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Administration of extracellular L-DOPA in a L-DOPA challenge model causes dramatic increase in DOPAC levels in GFP alone but not GFP-Rab3B expressing striatum as measured by microdialysis. Furthermore, overexpression of Rab3B increases both the number and size of synaptic vesicles in the synaptic terminals of these neurons.\n\n8/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known lipid anchor of the protein, the \"anchored component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Materials and methods: \"Female Sprague-Dawley rats weighing 200-250 g\n(Charles River Laboratories) were used in all animal experiments.\"\n\n8/2/2018 PIm\n- Overexpressed RAB3B is of unknown species. Authors contacted for species information (dd 8/2/2018, ole_isacson@hms.harvard.edu). Answer:\n\n\"Dear Prof Nierop,\nThank you for spearheading the SynGo project. I did answer the same email not so long ago but I'm wondering my email somehow did not reach you for some reason.\nThe RAB3B gene we used for the study was human (Homo Sapiens) origin.\nLet me know if you need any other information.\nThank you.\nChee Yeun\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0098993 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2431" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

